      "target": {
        "kind": "pull_request",
        "title": "refactor: move session/transcript runtime state to SQLite",
        "body": "## What\n\nMoves OpenClaw's **session, transcript, and runtime state off per-file `.jsonl`/JSON storage onto the SQLite state and agent databases**, brought fully up to date with current `main`. Channel plugins (Telegram, msteams, Matrix, Discord, etc.) persist through the plugin-state SDK keyed-store seam rather than touching the DB directly; storage-heavy plugins (memory-core, workboard) keep their own SQLite stores via SDK path helpers.\n\nThis is the **TypeScript-side** of the SQLite runtime work. It is complementary to (and disjoint from) the native/state-store cut in #81402 — both target `main` and can land independently.\n\n## Why\n\nThe previous design stored session/transcript/runtime state as many per-file `.jsonl`/JSON blobs. Consolidating onto SQLite gives transactional writes, consistent querying, and a single state surface, and lets channel plugins share one namespaced store instead of bespoke file formats.\n\n## Changes\n\n- Session/transcript reads & writes go through SQLite (`loadSqliteSessionTranscriptEvents`, `transcriptScope`, `session-entries.sqlite`, `transcript-store.sqlite`) — file-based session stores removed.\n- Generic plugin state persists via the plugin-state SDK keyed store (`plugin_state_entries`), namespaced per plugin.\n- Cron store, auth-profile state, exec-approvals, pairing, commitments, tasks, and related runtime state moved to the state DB.\n- Schemas in `src/state/*-schema.sql` (+ regenerated kysely types / generated TS).\n- Obsolete file-based state-migration subsystem removed in favor of `doctor/state-migrations`.\n\n## Testing\n\n- `pnpm tsgo:core` + `pnpm tsgo:core:test`: **0 errors**.\n- `pnpm build`: **green** (tsdown, plugin-sdk dts, ui, all postbuild phases).\n- Targeted suites pass in isolation; genuine migration bugs were found and fixed (commitments DB-init ordering, 3 gateway SQLite product bugs, cron-store-migration doctor tests).\n- **Known caveat:** the repo's `isolate: false` shards exhibit pre-existing cross-file test contamination locally (files pass in isolation; the failing set shuffles with `--sequence.shuffle.seed`). Full-suite certification should run on CI with proper isolation/sharding.\n",
        "branch": "josh/transcript-sqlite-migration",
